This function should return unique values but fails for objects:

```typescript
function unique<T>(arr: T[]): T[] {
    return [...new Set(arr)];
}
const result = unique([{id: 1}, {id: 1}]); // still 2 items
```

(Variant 34)

Bug: `Set` uses reference equality for objects, so identical objects are not deduplicated.
Fix: Use a Map with a serialized key for deduplication.

```typescript
function unique<T>(arr: T[], key: (item: T) => string): T[] {
    const seen = new Map<string, T>();
    for (const item of arr) {
        const k = key(item);
        if (!seen.has(k)) seen.set(k, item);
    }
    return [...seen.values()];
}
```

